activate().details: Self-activation function for validators, gaining `PendingActivation` status and setting next epoch as activation epoch to ensure rewards eligibility only after completing a full epoch

applyIncentives(uint32,(bytes,address,ui.details: The network's epoch issuance distribution method, rewarding stake originators proportionally to their share of total stake, tied to the validator's stake version

beginExit().details: Issues an exit request for a validator to be retired from the `Active` validator set

burn(address).details: In the case of malicious or erroneous node operator behavior, governance can use this function to burn a validator's `ConsensusNFT` and immediately eject from consensus committees if applicableIntended for sparing use; only reverts if burning results in empty committee

params.from: Refers to the struct member `ValidatorInfo.validatorAddress` in `IConsensusRegistry`

claimStakeRewards(address).details: Used by rewardees to claim staking rewards

concludeEpoch(address[],(uint24,uint232).details: Accepts the committee of voting validators for 2 epochs in the future

params.slashes: Slashes to the validators in the ending epoch, applied after rollover

delegateStake(bytes,address,bytes).details: Accepts delegated stake from a non-validator caller authorized by a validator's EIP712 signature

returns._0: _ EIP-712 typed struct hash used to enable delegated proof of stake

getCurrentEpochInfo().details: Returns the current epoch's committee and block height

getEpochInfo(uint32).details: Returns information about the provided epoch. Only four latest & two future epochs are stored

getRewards(address).details: Fetches the claimable rewards accrued for a given validator address

returns._0: _ The validator's claimable rewards, not including the validator's stake

getValidatorByTokenId(uint256).details: Fetches the `ValidatorInfo` for a given ConsensusNFT tokenId

getValidatorTokenId(address).details: Fetches the `tokenId` for a given validator validatorAddress

getValidators(uint8).details: Returns an array of unretired validators matching the provided status

params: `Active` queries also include validators pending activation or exit since all three remain eligible for committee service in the next epoch

incentiveInfo(address).details: Returns staking information for the given address

initialize(address,(uint256,uint256,uint.details: Only governance delegation is enabled at genesis

params.initialValidators_: The initial validator set running Telcoin Network; these validators will comprise the voter committee for the first three epochs, ie `epochInfo[0:2]`

isRetired(uint256).details: Returns whether validator associated with `tokenId` is exited && unstaked, ie "retired"

mint(address,uint256).details: The StakeManager's ERC721 ledger serves a permissioning role over validators, requiring Telcoin governance to approve each node operator and manually issue them a `ConsensusNFT`

params.to: Refers to the struct member `ValidatorInfo.validatorAddress` in `IConsensusRegistry`
params.tokenId: Refers to the `ERC721::tokenId` which must be less than `UNSTAKED` and nonzero tokenIds must be minted in order unless overwriting a retired validator for storage efficiency

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Emergency function to pause validator and stake management

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

stake(bytes).details: Accepts the native TEL stake amount from the calling validator, enabling later self-activation

totalSupply().details: Returns the current total supply of minted ConsensusNFTs

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Emergency function to unpause validator and stake management

unstake(address).details: Returns previously staked funds in addition to accrued rewards, if any, to the staker

upgradeStakeVersion((uint256,uint256,uin.details: Permissioned function to upgrade stake, withdrawal, and consensus block reward configurations

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

activate().notice: Caller must own a ConsensusNFT and be `Staked` status, ie staked or delegated

applyIncentives(uint32,(bytes,address,ui.notice: Slashing is not live but scaffolding for it is included here. For the time being, system calls to this function provide an empty calldata array

beginExit().notice: Reverts if the exit queue is full, ie if active validator count would drop too low

burn(address).notice: `from` will be marked `UNSTAKED` so the validator address cannot be reused

concludeEpoch(address[],(uint24,uint232).notice: Voting Validator Committee changes at the end every epoch via syscallSlashes are not currently used in TN mainnet alpha

delegateStake(bytes,address,bytes).notice: `validatorAddress` must be a validator already in possession of a `ConsensusNFT`

delegationDigest(bytes,address,address).notice: Returns the delegation digest that a validator should sign to accept a delegation

getEpochInfo(uint32).notice: When querying for future epochs, `blockHeight` will be 0 as they are not yet known

getValidatorByTokenId(uint256).notice: To enable checks against storage slots initialized to zero by the EVM, `tokenId` cannot be `0`

initialize(address,(uint256,uint256,uint.notice: Not actually used since this contract is precompiled and written to TN at genesis It is left in the contract for readable information about the relevant storage slots at genesis

isRetired(uint256).notice: Retired validators' ConsensusNFTs are burned, so existing tokenIds are invalid

mint(address,uint256).notice: Access-gated in ConsensusRegistry to its owner, which is a Telcoin governance address

pause().notice: Does not pause `concludeEpoch()`. Only accessible by `owner`

stake(bytes).notice: Caller must already have been issued a `ConsensusNFT` by Telcoin governance

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Consensus NFTs are soulbound to validators that mint them and cannot be transfered

unpause().notice: Does not affect `concludeEpoch()`. Only accessible by `owner`

unstake(address).notice: May only be called after fully exiting`IncentiveInfo::tokenId` will be set to `UNSTAKED` so the validator address cannot be reused

upgradeStakeVersion((uint256,uint256,uin.notice: The new version takes effect in the next epoch
